Sentencing hearing proceeded. Statements made as to sentencing.

As to COUNT 1 as AMENDED-
Court ordered defendant to serve 60 DAYS in the House of Correction; credit for 11 days time served. If revoked, defendant may have release for medical and treatment appointments.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 9 MONTHS with the following conditions:
1) Pay restitution in the amount of $1,000.00. $500.00 to be paid to Julie S-W. $500.00 to be paid to Karen K.;
2) Pay all costs, fees, surcharges, fines, and restitution during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. Defendant to enter into a payment plan with the agent;
3) Pay DNA surcharge;
4) Maintain absolute sobriety;
5) Pay $300.00 fine;
6) Perform 40 hours of community service at Project Return. Defendant to provide proof of completion to agent;
7) No driving without a valid license;

Upon successful completion of all condtions of probation, the Court will allow the defendant's term of probation to be terminated after six months. Early termination to be approved at the discretion of the agent.

Defendant posted $2,000.00 cash bail. $1,000.00 of the bail on deposit to be applied towards the restitution amounts. The remaining $1,000.00 cash bail on deposit to be returned to the poster. 

Court vacated the jury trial date of 10/05/15. 

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.

Defendant was remanded to the Court upon return of the warrant. Defendant previously posted $2,000.00 cash bail. Court ordered the cash bail on deposit be reinstated with turnover to Justice Point Monitoring. All conditions previously ordered remain the same, including:
- Drug testing;
- Maintain absolute sobriety;
- No possession or use of controlled substances without a valid prescription;
- No firearms/dangerous weapons;
- No contact with all victims in the criminal complaint;
